criteria.textblock:
        The inclusion criteria

          1. The patients were above 18 years-old;

          2. The patients were diagnosed with RA according to the American College of Rheumatology
             (ACR) criteria, and the current clinical state was in-active or relapse;

          3. The patients were consent to receive examinations of photoacoustic imaging.

        The exclusion criteria

          1. The patients had mental disease or other severe diseases, and were not capable of
             receiving imaging examinations;

          2. The patients had strong reaction to laser light.
